Ghana’s Accra Hearts of Oak Football Club to Its List Shares, JOY FM Says

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-07-18T08:27:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/ghana-s-accra-hearts-of-oak-football-club-to-its-list-shares-joy-fm-says.html
Accra Hearts of Oak, a football club
based in the Ghanaian capital, plans to raise 10 million cedis
selling shares on the city’s stock exchange on Aug. 1, Joy FM
reported.  The team, which will become the first Ghanaian football
club to list on the Ghana Stock Exchange, plans to sell 20
million shares at 50 pesewas each, the Accra-based radio station
said, citing Chairman E.M. Commodore Mensah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Moses Mozart Dzawu in Accra at 
 mdzawu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
